<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-24T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-24T07:00:00-05:00" n="421" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">865D.01/230: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-24T13:00:00+01:00">December 24, 1936—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 24—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>550. My 548, December 24, 11 a.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d421fn3">Not
                                    printed.</note> In view of the fact that 12 countries have
                                already given <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> recognition to the new
                                regime in Ethiopia, including all the great powers particularly
                                interested, can we not start the new year by some announcement to
                                the effect that the American Legation at Addis Ababa will shortly be
                                transformed into a consulate?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>